# Code & Frontend Style

## React
- Functional components + hooks. Prefer `const MyComponent = () => {}`.
- Use `"use client"` only when strictly required.
- Extract reusable logic into hooks (`useFetchForecast`, `useSpotData`) and pure utils.
- One responsibility per component; keep it testable.
- Callbacks clearly named (`handleClick`, `toggleModal`). Clean up effects.
- Explicit `loading` / `empty` / `error` states.

## Styling
- TailwindCSS for ALL styling. Do NOT add inline `style={{}}` (legacy `legacy-ui/*` violates this — migrate when you touch a file, don't add new inline styles).
- Prefer static Tailwind class names over dynamic class generation.

## TypeScript
- No `any` at module boundaries — type the data contract (the `hourlyData: any[]` UI boundary is a known debt; type new code).
- Prefer `unknown` + narrowing; derive types from a single source.

## Hygiene
- Never leave `console.log` in committed code.
- Accessibility: `aria-*`, labels, keyboard targets, responsive layout.
